originalText.text:
An unacceptable level of service and care.  I used Dr Leventhal because he was local and seemed to have good reviews.  But it'll take you multiple calls per day for multiple days to finally get thru and make an appointment (the receptionist is particularly rude, and seemingly annoyed every time you dare to ask for help).  Good luck getting prescriptions or any other medical help you may need when that time finally comes, a simple check up took me months to finally book and then attend.

I am now in the process of trying to switch to a professional doctor, and I can't even get my records/files from them, everytime I call the office they're either not there, or not able to do it.  Avoid.

originalText.text: Dr. Leventhal and Nadine are always warm and efficient.  The office is old-school, so most everything happens on paper or over the phone.  I know that I'm in good hands.
